    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.70-72_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">78</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Noel <hi rend="caps">W</hi> Harman
                        23885 Westwood Road
                        Westlake, Ohio
                        March 23, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute></opener> <p>It is with a deep sense of loss that I advise you of the death of my Father on March 16th.</p>
                
                <p>My Father had been recovering from high blood pressure when a coronary attack ended it all in a few moments. I attended the funeral service in Omaha on the 18th and just returned to-day.</p>
                
                <p>He was 74 years of age and in excellent health until about three months ago when this hypertension begin to <unclear>develop</unclear>.</p>
                
                <p>Father was more than just a dad to his and grandaughters since he was always one of us
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.70-72_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">71</fw>
                
                    with his youthful <unclear>vitality</unclear> and ready understanding of our problems.</p>
                
                <p>You may remember him as a young man of terrific energy and <unclear>drive</unclear> which he <unclear>retained</unclear> all through his life.</p>
                
                <p>At 60 he resigned an important job and joined another company where he quickly rose to a management position as Vice President.</p>
                
                <p>I have an original pencil drawing by <hi rend="caps">JAT HAMBIDOR</hi> which I <unclear>understand</unclear> you used as a <unclear>cover</unclear> plate on one of  your orginal books. I am sending it to you since Dad wanted you to have it when I lasted talked to him by long distance phone.</p>
                
                <p>My Father <unclear>gave</unclear> me many years of happiness and I shall always treasure his wonderful memory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                    
                    <signed><unclear>Noel</unclear></signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
